"{\"uid\": \"fansided.com-posts-watch-simone-biles-2024-paris-olympics\", \"entities\": [{\"sentence\": \"Simone Biles is one of the brightest stars on Team USA but entered the 2024 Paris Olympics with some big questions after her withdrawal from thw 2021 Tokyo games due to a bout of the \\\"twisties.\\\"\", \"from\": 0, \"to\": 194, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 0, \"end\": 12, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Simone_Biles\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Simone Biles\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Simone_Biles\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Simone_Biles\"}, {\"begin\": 46, \"end\": 54, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States_men's_national_basketball_team\", \"score\": 0.6407076712134653, \"rank\": 0.5607702737007731, \"text\": \"Team USA\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States_men's_national_basketball_team\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States_men's_national_basketball_team\"}, {\"begin\": 150, \"end\": 155, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tokyo_bid_for_the_2020_Summer_Olympics\", \"score\": 0.981743952202878, \"rank\": 0.018595294100250386, \"text\": \"Tokyo\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tokyo_bid_for_the_2020_Summer_Olympics\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tokyo_bid_for_the_2020_Summer_Olympics\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Since returning to competition she's been on a hot streak, looking in top form in the 2023 US and World Championships and at the US Olympic Trials.\", \"from\": 195, \"to\": 342, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 286, \"end\": 288, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States_men's_national_basketball_team\", \"score\": 0.9999959112466884, \"rank\": 4.073989932961364e-06, \"text\": \"US\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States_men's_national_basketball_team\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States_men's_national_basketball_team\"}, {\"begin\": 324, \"end\": 341, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States_Olympic_curling_trials\", \"score\": 0.9999999999035936, \"rank\": 8.605454948739679e-11, \"text\": \"US Olympic Trials\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States_Olympic_curling_trials\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States_Olympic_curling_trials\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Despite a lingering calf injury, Biles dominated in qualifying, setting herself up for appearances in the Team All-Around Final, the Individual All-Around Final, and the finals for the vault, balance beam and floor exercise.\", \"from\": 344, \"to\": 568, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"These events are all must-watch for any fan of gymnastics or just athletic greatness and they will be spread out over a full week.\", \"from\": 570, \"to\": 700, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"EVENT  DATE  TIME (ET)  Team All-Around Final  July 30  12:15 p.m.  Women's All-Around Final  August 1  12:15 p.m.\", \"from\": 702, \"to\": 816, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Vault Final  August 3  10:20 a.m.  Balance Beam Final  August 5  6:38 a.m.\", \"from\": 818, \"to\": 892, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 853, \"end\": 865, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Balance_beam\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 2.288796093468095e-50, \"text\": \"Balance Beam\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Balance_beam\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Balance_beam\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Floor Exercise Final  August 5  8:23 a.m.\", \"from\": 894, \"to\": 935, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"The times listed are when each event begins not necessarily when Biles will compete.\", \"from\": 937, \"to\": 1021, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"As one of the top qualifiers she will generally be going toward the end in each group.\", \"from\": 1022, \"to\": 1108, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Biles won the gold medal in four of these five events \\u00e2\\u0080\\u0094 team, individual, vault and floor exercise \\u00e2\\u0080\\u0094 at the 2016 Olympics in Rio de Janeiro.\", \"from\": 1109, \"to\": 1253, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1238, \"end\": 1252, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Rio_de_Janeiro\", \"score\": 0.9999999999934062, \"rank\": 6.596229279476888e-12, \"text\": \"Rio de Janeiro\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\", \"Q3957\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Rio_de_Janeiro\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Rio_de_Janeiro\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"She won bronze on the balance beam at those games and added a silver in the Team All-Around and a bronze on the balance beam at the 2021 games in Tokyo.\", \"from\": 1254, \"to\": 1406, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1400, \"end\": 1405, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tokyo_bid_for_the_2020_Summer_Olympics\", \"score\": 0.981743952202878, \"rank\": 0.018595294100250386, \"text\": \"Tokyo\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tokyo_bid_for_the_2020_Summer_Olympics\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tokyo_bid_for_the_2020_Summer_Olympics\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Winning gold in all five events this year would tie her with Larisa Latynina of Russia for the most gold medals by a female gymnast in Olympic history.\", \"from\": 1407, \"to\": 1558, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1468, \"end\": 1483, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Larisa_Latynina\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Larisa Latynina\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Larisa_Latynina\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Larisa_Latynina\"}, {\"begin\": 1487, \"end\": 1493, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Russia_men's_national_ice_hockey_team\", \"score\": 0.9992170682094358, \"rank\": 0.000712041532699159, \"text\": \"Russia\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Russia_men's_national_ice_hockey_team\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Russia_men's_national_ice_hockey_team\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Biles is not the only US gymnast witha chance to take him gold.\", \"from\": 1560, \"to\": 1623, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1582, \"end\": 1584, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States_men's_national_basketball_team\", \"score\": 0.9999959112466884, \"rank\": 4.073989932961364e-06, \"text\": \"US\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States_men's_national_basketball_team\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States_men's_national_basketball_team\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"In addition to the team competition, Suni Lee will compete in the All-Around Final and Balance Beam Final.\", \"from\": 1624, \"to\": 1730, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1661, \"end\": 1669, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Sunisa_Lee\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Suni Lee\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Sunisa_Lee\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Sunisa_Lee\"}, {\"begin\": 1711, \"end\": 1723, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Balance_beam\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 2.288796093468095e-50, \"text\": \"Balance Beam\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Balance_beam\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Balance_beam\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Jordan Chiles will be in the final for the floor exercise and Jade Carey will be in the final for the vault.\", \"from\": 1731, \"to\": 1839, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1731, \"end\": 1744, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jordan_Chiles\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Jordan Chiles\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jordan_Chiles\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jordan_Chiles\"}, {\"begin\": 1793, \"end\": 1803, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jad